8:
Let's have ourselves a wonderful
festival! No worrying about past or
future—tonight is all about the
PRESENT, hehe.
11:
Isn't that just like the tricks Nephtim
always does?
14:
Oho, not quite. I'm afraid these aren't
psychic powers... Competition's
tough these days, huh.
18:
Hmm, I suppose I'll have to step up
my game! Time for a Fool's Fantasy!
25:
You knocked it out of the park, Folus!
Great job!
28:
I was rather concerned at first, 
but I must admit... she exceeded all
expectations!
32:
Ohoho! What did I tell ya? I'm perfect
for the part.
36:
I'm a natural when it comes to
disguises, after all! I wear one all the
time.
41:
You do, huh? If that's how you are
normally, I can't imagine what
happens when you take off that
"disguise" of yours...
45:
Ohh? Do you often think about
taking off my clothes, Alk?
49:
I shouldn't have said that. 
I should NOT have said that.
55:
What's the matter? Having a hard
time falling asleep?
58:
Um, no, it's just... Today, my teacher
asked me to do something and I
didn't listen...
60:
Am I naughty? Will Santa come visit
me this year?
63:
Don't fret. I'll let you in on a little
secret—just between the two of us.
Small things like that don't bother
Santa.
67:
But the thing about Santa is... he
doesn't like to be seen! If you stay up
too late, he might skip you over!
70: Oh no! Okay, I'll go sleep right away.
77:
Apologies for the embarrassing
sight you just had to witness.
81:
Embarrassing? No way! That was
just about the sweetest thing you
could have done!
84:
No doubt about it—this place is
blessed.
90:
But can the same be said of these
murky, starless skies?
93: What do you think, your highness?
97:
Do not call me that—as I've told you
multiple times, our people no longer
have a king.
99:
Which means we have no need of
jesters either. What is your business
with me?
105:
Happy Holidays! I come bearing
gifts—cake, prepared especially by
the chef boy wonder Alk himself!
Fancy a bite?
113:
This holiday of theirs is really
something, huh? They celebrate
their young by giving them presents.
We oughta celebrate something too!
116:
How about the Lord of Shadow's
birthday? Er, wait, that's no good.
Maybe the day of his defeat instead?
121:
Neither of those would serve any
use. But I do agree that we are in
need of some sort of holiday.
126:
Ah-HAH! Now we're getting
somewhere. Well, Mr.
Definitely-Not-A-King, if ya could
push that up on your agenda, 
I'd appreciate it!
128:
And while you're at it, I figure it might
be time to let everyone know the
truth, dontcha think?
132:
That poor Pandemonium's on the
verge of being gobbled up by the
abyss. Along with that other land we
worked so hard to get.
135:
No future for the fiends—womp
womp womp! Am I right, 
or am I right?
140:
...So, the fool fancies herself a
prophet, does she?
145:
Ah-HAH! My bad, that was a bit
extreme. Let me rephrase it—the
fiends have no worthwhile future
they can believe in!
150:
It falls to me to give our people 
a vision of that future.
154:
Ooh. Maybe like—and I'm just
throwing this out there—how a king
would?
157:
Things used to be simple! I'm sure
you remember—as long as we kept
killing humans, we were set!
160:
I guess Oghir was a bit different. He
had that whole spiel about
immortality being our only salvation,
right?
163:
But it's all the same, really! Pretty
little lies to keep us mindlessly on
the path forward.
167:
Will you do the same? Will you
"make" us believe?
172:
...There's no need to do anything like
that.
175:
The future I lead our people to will
be a feasible one—step by step, we
will march toward a goal within our
means.
178:
We have need of but one thing: the
will to carry on and see our task to
its completion.
183: So "will" is really all it takes, then?
187:
Don't tell me you don't understand. 
I know you've encountered 
the type of will I speak of.
190:
...But it is true that we aren't making
good time. My work with Lilith Stratos
must continue. When we are
finished, come see me again.
195:
...You find it difficult to stomach lies,
don't you?
200:
What? Me? I'm a JESTER, Mr. No-King!
Lies are part and parcel of who we
are! Ah-HAH!
205:
The cake was delicious. You and the
boy have my thanks. Tell him I'll
come visit him when I find a spare
moment.
213:
Ahahaha! Now that's a farce I can
get behind!
